I'll take you a part of the road.

998
01:49:40,036 --> 01:49:43,037
for you scarce put one
foot in front of the other.

999
01:49:43,678 --> 01:49:45,759
Ride with me I say.

1000
01:49:50,040 --> 01:49:52,600
Ah? But I know you.

1001
01:49:54,402 --> 01:49:57,322
You are that Mr Stokes-
D'Uberville's fancy woman.

1002
01:49:58,083 --> 01:50:02,084
You weren't too proud
to cock-a-leg for Groby.

1003
01:50:05,606 --> 01:50:07,286
Trollop!

1004
01:50:24,013 --> 01:50:25,574
If it isn't my little Tess.

1005
01:50:32,617 --> 01:50:35,817
Oh poor poppet. What a state you are in.

1006
01:50:37,499 --> 01:50:39,420
You are so cold!

1007
01:50:45,141 --> 01:50:48,062
Here. Get that inside you

1008
01:50:48,663 --> 01:50:49,983
This will warm your bones

1009
01:50:52,665 --> 01:50:54,345
Go on my love. Drink it.

1010
01:51:04,348 --> 01:51:05,349
Get it out

1011
01:51:06,671 --> 01:51:08,550
You mustn't let yourself go.

1012
01:51:08,751 --> 01:51:10,671
Even bad luck runs out in the end.

1013
01:51:11,271 --> 01:51:12,511
Take my word for it.

1014
01:51:13,232 --> 01:51:14,433
I can't go on.

1015
01:51:14,953 --> 01:51:16,673
You'll feel better tomorrow.

1016
01:51:17,114 --> 01:51:21,595
OH no. I can't go on. My life...

1017
01:51:24,757 --> 01:51:27,597
If I had the courage, I'd like to die.

1018
01:51:28,279 --> 01:51:30,479
Don't talk such flubbery.

1019
01:51:31,599 --> 01:51:33,600
Why didn't you come and see me sooner?

1020
01:51:34,880 --> 01:51:36,400
Eh? I could have taken you in here, my girl.

1021
01:51:36,842 --> 01:51:37,722
Is there still some work here.

1022
01:51:38,042 --> 01:51:39,802
In this wretched place?

1023
01:51:41,003 --> 01:51:43,843
There's always work here.

1024
01:51:53,808 --> 01:51:56,329
Come... have some
of my nice soup.

1025
01:52:02,131 --> 01:52:06,052
After that, we must
take off those slum,

1026
01:52:06,574 --> 01:52:10,054
mirky clothes and
prettify yourself. Eh?

1027
01:52:17,138 --> 01:52:19,898
Just to make me jealous again, hey?

1028
01:52:22,620 --> 01:52:23,659
WEll, Tessy.

1029
01:53:42,970 --> 01:53:43,970
Are you the new hand?

1030
01:53:53,215 --> 01:53:55,615
T'was you was it?

1031
01:53:58,736 --> 01:54:00,217
Is that all you've done?

1032
01:54:01,057 --> 01:54:02,537
T'is a mighty poor show.

1033
01:54:03,058 --> 01:54:04,538
She's not accustomed to it.

1034
01:54:04,698 --> 01:54:06,218
I don't keep useless hands here.

1035
01:54:06,740 --> 01:54:07,940
I'm not payed for what we do.

1036
01:54:08,220 --> 01:54:09,580
So where's the difference?

1037
01:54:09,740 --> 01:54:10,500
No arguing.

1038
01:54:10,701 --> 01:54:12,021
I want the whole lot cleared.

1039
01:54:12,621 --> 01:54:13,262
Well, it's too late.

1040
01:54:14,742 --> 01:54:15,862
You'd better.

1041
01:54:24,386 --> 01:54:25,826
Now, you not mind Groby.

1042
01:54:27,147 --> 01:54:28,188
T'is just as well.

1043
01:54:28,707 --> 01:54:30,148
Ah... I know lord loves us.

1044
01:54:30,708 --> 01:54:32,148
but it's not like it was at the dairy.

1045
01:54:32,829 --> 01:54:34,550
Dairyman on the deck all the week,

1046
01:54:35,430 --> 01:54:37,310
On Sundays he's the Mr Richard Crick!

1047
01:55:37,135 --> 01:55:39,094
It don't do to pray here missy.

1048
01:55:43,216 --> 01:55:44,897
There's been a curse on this place.

1049
01:55:47,378 --> 01:55:48,939
This is the Cross-in-hand, isn't it?

1050
01:55:49,139 --> 01:55:50,258
Aye. So it is.

1051
01:55:51,860 --> 01:55:54,781
On the count of a malefactor
they tortured here, in ancient times

1052
01:55:55,020 --> 01:56:00,143
they did nail his hand onto the
post and then they hangged him.

1053
01:56:01,424 --> 01:56:05,105
The bones are down
there to this day I'm told.

1054
01:58:45,967 --> 01:58:46,927
OH!

1055
01:58:49,848 --> 01:58:50,688
What have you found?

1056
01:58:51,530 --> 01:58:53,250
An old pair of boots.

1057
01:58:59,292 --> 01:59:00,693
STill in good condition.

1058
01:59:04,574 --> 01:59:06,054
Could be of use to the poor.

1059
02:00:01,396 --> 02:00:03,036
There! Have a look.

1060
02:00:52,216 --> 02:00:54,377
I knew nothing of your circumstances.

1061
02:00:54,736 --> 02:00:57,617
Nothing at all until your mother wrote to me.

1062
02:00:57,818 --> 02:00:58,498
My mother?

1063
02:00:58,738 --> 02:01:01,778
She wrote what you should
have told me a long time ago.

1064
02:01:03,420 --> 02:01:04,460
I came at once.

1065
02:01:07,022 --> 02:01:07,862
Tess...

1066
02:01:16,546 --> 02:01:17,906
Why did you never say anything?

1067
02:01:18,346 --> 02:01:19,987
I had nothing to ask of you.

1068
02:01:21,266 --> 02:01:22,147
That isn't so.

1069
02:01:23,788 --> 02:01:27,269
You wear your ridiculous pride like a h

1070
02:01:28,070 --> 02:01:30,511
And you put me even more
in the wrong than I was!

1071
02:01:31,430 --> 02:01:32,510
Against my will

1072
02:01:34,032 --> 02:01:36,113
I have done my duty for my child.

1073
02:01:37,393 --> 02:01:38,713
On my honour i did it.

1074
02:01:39,393 --> 02:01:40,474
honour...

1075
02:01:42,396 --> 02:01:44,676
I want to take you away
from this wretched place.

1076
02:01:45,035 --> 02:01:46,076
Somewhere you're worthy of.

1077
02:01:47,238 --> 02:01:51,518
What is this strange temptation
that misery holds for you?

1078
02:01:52,399 --> 02:01:54,119
Come to your senses.

1079
02:01:54,920 --> 02:01:55,960
Come away with me.

1080
02:02:01,402 --> 02:02:02,322
your father's ill.

1081
02:02:02,443 --> 02:02:03,204
Did you know?

1082
02:02:04,163 --> 02:02:04,804
yes...

1083
02:02:05,644 --> 02:02:07,604
they fear the worst.

1084
02:02:08,205 --> 02:02:11,405
your family will be evicted if he dies.

1085
02:02:14,167 --> 02:02:16,247
I'm offering you my help sincerely.

1086
02:02:18,329 --> 02:02:19,569
Noone else seems to care.

1087
02:02:21,249 --> 02:02:23,810
Who is this husband of yours?

1088
02:02:24,932 --> 02:02:26,171
How can he abandon you like this?

1089
02:02:27,293 --> 02:02:29,173
Tess!

1090
02:04:52,309 --> 02:04:55,869
There's a point beyond
which obstinity becomes stupedity.

1091
02:04:59,471 --> 02:05:01,431
Are you in love with this drudgery?

1092
02:05:04,473 --> 02:05:06,113
I may be a sham-D'Urberville

1093
02:05:06,433 --> 02:05:08,274
but my little finger can
do more for you than

1094
02:05:08,554 --> 02:05:09,835
your blue-blooded ancestors.

1095
02:05:13,917 --> 02:05:17,437
I'm right. You know I am.

1096
02:05:23,120 --> 02:05:24,881
Forget about all this

1097
02:05:26,281 --> 02:05:27,121
and forget about that mule

1098
02:05:27,562 --> 02:05:28,802
that you call your husband.

1099
02:05:33,164 --> 02:05:36,765
Go on. Hit me. I shall not cry out.

1100
02:05:38,446 --> 02:05:40,367
Once beckon...
always beckon again.

1101
02:05:41,206 --> 02:05:42,006
That's law.

1102
02:05:42,769 --> 02:05:43,768
I was your master once

1103
02:05:46,489 --> 02:05:47,209
and so shall be again.

1104
02:05:49,650 --> 02:05:53,011
If you are any man's wife,
you are mine.

1105
02:05:55,092 --> 02:05:56,293
My own dear husband.

1106
02:05:57,654 --> 02:06:00,255
I shall die soon unless
I get a word from you.

1107
02:06:01,656 --> 02:06:03,856
All my letter have
remained unanswered.

1108
02:06:05,736 --> 02:06:08,057
Have you even received them?

1109
02:06:10,018 --> 02:06:14,179
I long for one thing only.
And that is to see you again.

1110
02:06:15,460 --> 02:06:16,580
Come back to me Angel.

1111
02:06:17,902 --> 02:06:21,062
Come back to me and save me
from the thing that threatens me.

1112
02:06:55,516 --> 02:06:59,436
Any reasonable person would
call this a ludicrous situation.

1113
02:07:01,038 --> 02:07:04,558
I offered to help you.
You wanned all of that.

1114
02:07:05,920 --> 02:07:09,360
You prefer to turnyourself into gypsies.

1115
02:07:10,121 --> 02:07:10,602
Please go.

1116
02:07:11,402 --> 02:07:14,402
In other words, Mrs. Clare,
you are asking me to let

1117
02:07:14,643 --> 02:07:15,604
you starve in peace.

1118
02:07:15,843 --> 02:07:16,843
Go away!

1119
02:07:18,525 --> 02:07:20,245
You'll be civil yet.

1120
02:07:28,049 --> 02:07:30,289
What's to become of me
and my poor little mites?

1121
02:07:31,571 --> 02:07:33,450
WE be the D'Urberville family.

1122
02:07:33,691 --> 02:07:34,771
It's written there isn't it?

1123
02:07:35,211 --> 02:07:37,812
Oh yeah... it's written there
fine enough. I grant you.

1124
02:07:38,292 --> 02:07:39,493
But the rooms have been taken.

1125
02:07:40,373 --> 02:07:41,653
You never sent in your deposits.

1126
02:07:42,974 --> 02:07:45,374
He means the money to
pay for the account, mother.

1127
02:07:46,175 --> 02:07:48,055
There's more to life than money sir!

1128
02:07:48,977 --> 02:07:51,897
You can not leave these poor,
fatherless children in the streets.

1129
02:07:52,338 --> 02:07:53,179
It would be a crime!

1130
02:07:53,418 --> 02:07:53,859
Missus...

1131
02:07:54,059 --> 02:07:56,339
Hospitality is sacred,
even among the Pagan Turks!

1132
02:07:56,700 --> 02:07:58,340
Please Missus... tis your own fault.

1133
02:07:58,701 --> 02:07:59,701
We'll see about that.

1134
02:08:00,301 --> 02:08:02,781
We are a true descendents
of the knightly D'Urbervilles.

1135
02:08:03,182 --> 02:08:05,462
Nobody leaves us in
the streets like raw apples.

1136
02:08:05,703 --> 02:08:08,903
Not in the home of our ancestors.
Our boards are in the

1137
02:08:09,104 --> 02:08:10,865
crip there laid out there in their carpets.

1138
02:08:11,064 --> 02:08:11,744
what's with you...

1139
02:08:12,146 --> 02:08:15,266
No, my dear. What's true is true.
Your poor father's eyes

1140
02:08:15,547 --> 02:08:17,107
are on us. We mustn't shame him.

1141
02:08:18,468 --> 02:08:21,789
Oh lord protect his own.
On the weekly champ he punished.

1142
02:08:22,470 --> 02:08:23,749
Ladies stopping here then?

1143
02:08:24,270 --> 02:08:25,870
no my good man. we are going on.

1144
02:08:26,632 --> 02:08:27,751
Good man... good man...

1145
02:08:28,232 --> 02:08:30,432
I ought to get by to Marlott.

1146
02:08:50,239 --> 02:08:51,080
Unload Darrell.

1147
02:08:51,520 --> 02:08:52,040
Where?

1148
02:08:52,321 --> 02:08:52,721
Here!

1149
02:08:53,041 --> 02:08:53,842
Here?

1150
02:08:54,082 --> 02:08:54,682
Yes Here.

1151
02:08:55,202 --> 02:08:56,922
We shall camp beside our church

1152
02:08:57,443 --> 02:08:58,764
until the town of our ancestors,

1153
02:08:59,003 --> 02:08:59,843
Find us our shelters.

1154
02:09:00,484 --> 02:09:02,444
Now come on children.
Set to work.

1155
02:10:44,804 --> 02:10:46,845
Why am I on the
wrong side of this door?

1156
02:11:59,073 --> 02:11:59,553
Yeah!

1157
02:11:59,993 --> 02:12:02,194
It's me Father, Angel!

1158
02:12:14,279 --> 02:12:16,959
My boy, my poor boy.

1159
02:12:17,280 --> 02:12:19,401
I've been ill but I'm alright now.

1160
02:12:36,648 --> 02:12:39,448
Why have you treated me
so monstrously Angel?

1161
02:12:40,489 --> 02:12:44,929
I do not deserve it.
I have thought it over carefully

1162
02:12:46,131 --> 02:12:48,411
and I can never, never forgive you.

1163
02:12:49,652 --> 02:12:53,653
You are cruel. I shall try to forget you.

1164
02:12:54,654 --> 02:12:58,735
All I ever received of
your hands is injustice.

1165
02:14:20,647 --> 02:14:22,088
Mr Durbeyfield.

1166
02:14:24,729 --> 02:14:26,290
Beg your pardon?

1167
02:14:26,930 --> 02:14:27,931
You are Mr Durbeyfield?

1168
02:14:29,491 --> 02:14:31,491
They don't live here no more.

1169
02:14:31,652 --> 02:14:32,693
Since when?

1170
02:14:33,812 --> 02:14:35,173
Since John Durbeyfield died.

1171
02:14:36,493 --> 02:14:37,813
Do you know where they went?

1172
02:14:51,419 --> 02:14:54,019
Durbeyfield... from 1832 to 1888

1173
02:14:54,901 --> 02:14:57,461
more properly D'Urberville of once

1174
02:14:57,782 --> 02:14:58,782
powerful family of that name

1175
02:14:59,823 --> 02:15:01,943
and directly descended
through illustrious lines

1176
02:15:02,184 --> 02:15:05,545
of Pagan D'Urberville.
Likes of a conqueror.

1177
02:15:06,025 --> 02:15:07,265
How are the mighty fallen?

1178
02:15:08,827 --> 02:15:10,546
Ah yes... how indeed.

1179
02:15:11,267 --> 02:15:13,227
May I? for the poor.

1180
02:15:15,349 --> 02:15:17,068
I prefer to settle
the Mason's account.

1181
02:15:18,230 --> 02:15:20,270
You'd think he's never
been paid for his work.

1182
02:15:22,752 --> 02:15:23,912
They were an odd family.

1183
02:15:24,512 --> 02:15:25,992
My collegue Mr Tringham,
would have done

1184
02:15:26,273 --> 02:15:27,512
better to have kept his mouth shut.

1185
02:16:02,727 --> 02:16:04,928
I should like to see Mrs Clare.

1186
02:16:08,090 --> 02:16:08,850
Tess

1187
02:16:10,170 --> 02:16:12,170
Yes I know. She's not here.

1188
02:16:13,811 --> 02:16:15,092
You are Mrs. Durbeyfield.

1189
02:16:16,371 --> 02:16:17,132
Yes

1190
02:16:18,253 --> 02:16:19,133
Where is she living?

1191
02:16:20,293 --> 02:16:21,014
I don't know.

1192
02:16:22,775 --> 02:16:23,695
I'm her husband.

1193
02:16:24,776 --> 02:16:26,095
I guessed as much.

1194
02:16:27,737 --> 02:16:28,857
Then tell me where she is.

1195
02:16:29,857 --> 02:16:30,817
Please, tell me.

1196
02:16:31,178 --> 02:16:34,338
Leave her. Leave her in peace.

1197
02:16:35,179 --> 02:16:37,340
My poor girl's suffered enough.

1198
02:16:38,701 --> 02:16:41,782
She don't care to see you sir. Never.

1199
02:16:57,388 --> 02:16:59,109
Mrs Durbeyfield,

1200
02:16:59,749 --> 02:17:01,909
take pity on a lonely,
wretched man.

1201
02:17:02,070 --> 02:17:03,510
Tell me where to find her.

1202
02:17:05,150 --> 02:17:05,911
I beg you.

1203
02:17:07,952 --> 02:17:08,873
She's at Sandbourne.

1204
02:17:09,072 --> 02:17:11,353
Sandbourne? But where?

1205
02:17:11,714 --> 02:17:13,194
It's a large town these days.

1206
02:17:13,514 --> 02:17:16,155
That's all I know. Sandbourne.

1207
02:17:44,566 --> 02:17:45,406
Excuse me.

1208
02:17:46,567 --> 02:17:48,127
I'm looking for a Mrs. Clare.

1209
02:17:48,728 --> 02:17:50,689
Would you by any
chance know her address?

1210
02:17:53,370 --> 02:17:56,811
Ah, George. You got a Clare around?

1211
02:17:59,412 --> 02:18:01,773
No... we've had a lot of
visitors here. You know.

1212
02:18:02,013 --> 02:18:03,414
Or Durbeyfield. Miss Durbeyfield.

1213
02:18:03,774 --> 02:18:05,054
D'Urberville at the Herons.

1214
02:18:05,294 --> 02:18:05,934
That's it. D'Urberville.

1215
02:18:06,334 --> 02:18:08,494
It's a boarding house sir. Can't miss it.

1216
02:18:08,696 --> 02:18:09,295
Where abouts?

1217
02:19:04,157 --> 02:19:04,677
Yes?

1218
02:19:05,317 --> 02:19:06,957
Please excuse me
for calling at this hour.

1219
02:19:07,838 --> 02:19:10,559
But do you have a Teresa
D'Urberville staying in your board?

1220
02:19:11,039 --> 02:19:12,160
Mrs D'Urberville you mean?

1221
02:19:12,841 --> 02:19:13,521
Yes.

1222
02:19:14,681 --> 02:19:15,401
Please come in.

1223
02:19:21,043 --> 02:19:22,604
Would be kind enough to
tell her that her relative

1224
02:19:22,804 --> 02:19:23,644
is anxious to see her?

1225
02:19:23,965 --> 02:19:25,765
It's rather early sir. What name shall I give?

1226
02:19:26,085 --> 02:19:26,845
Angel.

1227
02:19:27,326 --> 02:19:28,006
Mr Angel?

1228
02:19:28,327 --> 02:19:31,047
Angel. It's my christian name.
She'll understand.

1229
02:19:37,730 --> 02:19:40,131
I'll go and see if she's awake.

1230
02:20:40,674 --> 02:20:44,275
Tess. I came to ask your forgiveness.

1231
02:20:48,637 --> 02:20:49,597
It's too late.

1232
02:20:51,238 --> 02:20:54,238
Too late? My darling wife.

1233
02:20:55,640 --> 02:20:56,880
I've come to fetch you.
I'm going to...

1234
02:20:57,561 --> 02:21:00,122
Don't come near me Angel please.

1235
02:21:02,923 --> 02:21:05,764
Too Late. Too Late.

1236
02:21:07,245 --> 02:21:11,526
I'm not the man I was. I've suffered too.

1237
02:21:13,767 --> 02:21:15,407
I humbly beg you to forgive me.

1238
02:21:18,009 --> 02:21:24,411
Yes. yes... But I tell you it's too late.

1239
02:21:28,853 --> 02:21:31,213
Don't you know at all? Don't you?

1240
02:21:34,095 --> 02:21:35,975
How did you find your way here?

1241
02:21:38,497 --> 02:21:39,337
I saw your mother.

1242
02:21:44,019 --> 02:21:45,539
I waited and waited for you.

1243
02:21:46,499 --> 02:21:47,379
But you didn't come.

1244
02:21:49,301 --> 02:21:51,141
I wrote to you. But you didn't come.

1245
02:21:55,423 --> 02:21:58,263
He has been good tome.
To all of us.

1246
02:22:02,786 --> 02:22:06,467
He's won me back to him.
He's upstairs.

1247
02:22:10,988 --> 02:22:13,709
Go now Angel. Go please.

1248
02:22:16,832 --> 02:22:18,792
Never come back anymore.

1249
02:23:44,945 --> 02:23:45,905
Good morning my dear

1250
02:24:00,672 --> 02:24:01,711
WEll, what's the matter now?

1251
02:24:06,553 --> 02:24:07,513
You feeling unwell?

1252
02:24:09,435 --> 02:24:10,595
Is that why you have the vapours?

1253
02:24:12,996 --> 02:24:16,917
Yes? No?

1254
02:24:20,239 --> 02:24:24,199
yes I know. You are moping as usual.

1255
02:24:28,402 --> 02:24:32,203
For god's sake, try and make an effort.

1256
02:24:39,566 --> 02:24:41,006
Did you have a bad dream?

1257
02:24:47,969 --> 02:24:49,491
Brazil perhaps?

1258
02:25:07,177 --> 02:25:10,018
These mooning hysterics
of yours are in poor taste.

1259
02:25:14,060 --> 02:25:15,941
Don't forget we are
lunching with the Bennets.

1260
02:25:16,941 --> 02:25:18,302
I'd like you to look presentable.

1261
02:25:21,342 --> 02:25:22,983
A genuine D'Urberville.

1262
02:27:28,951 --> 02:27:31,392
I came to tell you that I killed him.

1263
02:27:38,956 --> 02:27:40,076
I've done it.

1264
02:27:41,997 --> 02:27:42,998
I don't know how

1265
02:27:47,079 --> 02:27:48,040
I don't know.

1266
02:27:49,919 --> 02:27:52,160
I tried to rake him with my glove put

1267
02:27:53,761 --> 02:27:55,122
the blood in his mouth

1268
02:27:57,123 --> 02:27:58,803
I thought I might be capable of it

1269
02:28:01,484 --> 02:28:06,445
Yes... yes. It was from that day on

1270
02:28:07,567 --> 02:28:08,327
What's mean?

1271
02:28:10,007 --> 02:28:11,328
I've killed him

1272
02:28:21,412 --> 02:28:22,651
I won't desert you.

1273
02:28:23,613 --> 02:28:26,093
I shall protect you by
every means in my power.

1274
02:28:27,335 --> 02:28:29,375
Whatever you may or may
not have done, I love you.

1275
02:28:29,935 --> 02:28:31,495
I love you.

1276
02:28:33,177 --> 02:28:34,217
Will they hang me?

1277
02:28:44,300 --> 02:28:47,021
WE must get out at the next
station and head north on foot.

1278
02:28:48,462 --> 02:28:50,223
They'll be looking for us at the Wessex ports.

1279
02:28:51,784 --> 02:28:53,625
Once we reach the north
we'll go abroad.

1280
02:29:45,124 --> 02:29:46,405
WE have makings of a mule here.

1281
02:29:47,126 --> 02:29:48,006
and a bottle of wine.

1282
02:32:41,993 --> 02:32:43,193
Rest at last.

1283
02:36:36,202 --> 02:36:38,083
We must leave at once.

1284
02:36:42,526 --> 02:36:46,767
WE must leave here as soon as possible.

1285
02:36:48,328 --> 02:36:51,769
My life couldn't be a matter of weeks?

1286
02:36:53,450 --> 02:36:54,610
Why not wait for them here?

1287
02:36:56,010 --> 02:36:57,931
Since they'll catch me in any case.

1288
02:36:59,091 --> 02:37:00,172
I'm going to save you.

1289
02:37:00,692 --> 02:37:01,413
Do you hear?

1290
02:37:01,973 --> 02:37:03,173
I'm going to save you.

1291
02:38:22,844 --> 02:38:24,044
Can't we rest here?

1292
02:38:25,165 --> 02:38:29,166
I'm afraid not. By day this place
is visible from miles around.

1293
02:38:32,208 --> 02:38:34,049
There are no stars tonight.

1294
02:38:39,131 --> 02:38:41,971
Perhaps we could have made
our souls take flight together.

1295
02:38:51,535 --> 02:38:53,295
Do they sacrifice to god here?

1296
02:38:54,536 --> 02:38:58,377
No . To the sun I believe. It's a Pagan temple.

1297
02:39:01,899 --> 02:39:03,140
Older than the ages.

1298
02:39:06,101 --> 02:39:07,460
Older than the D'Urbervilles.

1299
02:39:16,464 --> 02:39:18,865
Do you think we shall meet again after death?

1300
02:39:26,868 --> 02:39:29,229
I'm afraid Angel. I'm afraid.

1301
02:40:38,977 --> 02:40:40,337
There's no use sir.

1302
02:40:41,297 --> 02:40:42,817
The whole country's roused.

1303
02:40:58,345 --> 02:41:02,465
She's sleeping. Just a little longer.

1304
02:41:21,272 --> 02:41:22,713
Have they come for me?

1305
02:41:23,994 --> 02:41:25,515
Yes.

1306
02:41:40,000 --> 02:41:41,400
I'm ready.
